  "texts": [
    "For the set-up with no pretraining, we decay the learning rate from 0.01 to 0.001 in 1,000,000 steps.",
    "We do not perform any hyperparameter tuning.",
    "These hyperparameter values are either selected to be a large round number (training steps) or are provided by default in the Meliad codebase.",
    "Because the language model decoding process returns k different sequences describing k alternative auxiliary constructions, we perform a beam search over these k options, using the score of each beam as its value function.",
    "This set-up is highly parallelizable across beams, allowing substantial speed-up when there are parallel computational resources."
  ],
